word_mean_info__list.difference: 指坚持不懈、毫不动摇地紧跟、追赶某人、某物或某个事业。
指根据线索或足迹进行跟踪。用于抽象意义时指找到某事物的根源。
指沿着人或动物留下的印迹或行迹追踪。
原义为“追猎、猎取”，现用于指追捕或搜寻逃犯等。
指快速追赶或决心追踪，褒义贬义均可用。
普遍用词，含义最广，多指跟随起引导作用的人或物，跟随的动机可以是善意的，也可能是恶意的。

依稀可见的踪迹；微弱痕迹

bilingual.source: There is a trace of chili in this dish.
bilingual.target: 这道菜里有微量的辣椒。

bilingual.source: There is a trace of alcohol in his blood.
bilingual.target: 他的血液中有微量的酒精。

bilingual.source: This medicine contains a trace of a certain chemical.
bilingual.target: 这药物中含有微量的某种化学物质。

bilingual.source: They detected a trace of metal in the ancient artifact.
bilingual.target: 他们在古代文物中检测到了微量的金属。

bilingual.source: Scientists found a trace of pollutants in the water sample.
bilingual.target: 科学家在水样中发现了微量的污染物。

bilingual.source: Gas chromatography can detect trace components in samples.
bilingual.target: 气相色谱法可以检测样品中的微量成分。

bilingual.source: Through spectral analysis, we can detect trace elements.
bilingual.target: 通过光谱分析，我们可以检测到微量元素。

bilingual.source: Through energy spectrum analysis, we can detect trace elements.
bilingual.target: 通过能谱分析，我们可以检测到微量元素。

bilingual.source: Electroanalysis is used to detect trace amounts of metals in water.
bilingual.target: 电化学分析用于检测水中微量金属。

bilingual.source: Scientists use high performance liquid chromatography to detect trace components in samples.
bilingual.target: 科学家们使用高效液相色谱来检测样品中的微量成分。

list.abstract: trace是一个计算机术语。TRACE和TRACK是用来调试web服务器连接的HTTP方式。TRACE宏对于VC下程序调试来说是很有用的东西，有着类似printf的功能。在MATLAB中，trace用于求二维方阵的迹，即该方阵对角线上元素之和。在Flex中，用作调试信息显示函数，用于在debug（调试）模式下输出。
《Trace》是一部由韩在林PD执导的电影，改编自同名网络人气漫画。

yingyinNormal.en: Sometimes, these confessions are hoaxes but based on his story, we were able to return to the lake site where we discovered trace DNA matching that of Mr. Cartoff in critical areas of the search zone.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有时候，这些认罪行为是恶作剧但是根据他的描述，我们回到我们发现微量DNA的湖的位置，这些DNA被证实与卡托夫先生的相吻合，同时这个湖是在搜寻区的关键位置。

yingyinNormal.en: A small trace of your DNA. There, I just left a small trace of my DNA.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一些你DNA的痕迹，我刚在那儿留下了一些我的DNA痕迹。

yingyinNormal.en: Do I need to keep them engaged so you can trace the call?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我需要拖住他们好让你们追踪通话吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Well, I would trace it to the Edward Snowden leak around June 10.
yingyinNormal.zh: 可以追溯到斯诺登泄密事件，六月十日左右吧。

yingyinNormal.en: I'll trace the calls Walter got. I'm taking this back to the eighth.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我去追踪沃尔特接到的电话。我把这个带回第八分局。

yingyinNormal.en: Every form he's built, every trace of his presence on the net. We have to act now.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他制造的机器，他在网络上的一切痕迹，我们必须马上行动。

yingyinNormal.en: We trace out small portions of sea and transform estuaries into private concessions.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们划出一小部分海域，将河口变为私人领地。

yingyinNormal.en: You can't trace it. Oh, you couldn't. Until Mt. Gox was bankrupted. The Bitcoin exchange.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不能追踪其流向。之前是不能追踪，但Mt.Gox破产了，那家比特币交易平台。

yingyinNormal.en: But you hang up seconds before I can trace it and then I say, "I'm getting too old for this crud"?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们却在定位成功的前几秒挂了，让我说出"我太老了，力不从心了"的桥段。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, ma'am, if you were to touch it in the same place, a small trace of my cells may end up on you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 女士，如果你也触碰这里，我的细胞就会转移到你身上。

yingyinNormal.en: He wants you to find it. It's been taken. It emits a gamma signature that's too weak for us to trace.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他希望你能找到它，魔方被抢了，目前它散发的伽马射线太微弱，我们追踪不到。

yingyinNormal.en: He's been asking people, hoping to trace that trait across the whole city to see if he can find his birth parent.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他一直在到处问，希望在整个城市中找出会卷舌头的人看看能不能找到自己的亲生父母。

yingyinNormal.en: Then law enforcement was suddenly allowed access to the servers, which meant that we could trace the Bitcoin to Robbie's computer.
yingyinNormal.zh: 之后执法部门突然就允许进入服务器了，这意味着我们可以追踪比特币流向，直到罗比的电脑。

yingyinNormal.en: Chechnya 2013. Insurgents turned on one another. Indisputable, the work of our mercenaries but no trace of any chemicals of any kind.
yingyinNormal.zh: 2013年，车臣，叛乱分子相互攻击。毫无疑问，也是这些雇佣兵的杰作，但没有查出任何化学制品。

yingyinNormal.en: Here's the thing about DNA. whatever you touch, whether you pick up a soda can, or a garden hose, you leave a small trace of yourself.
yingyinNormal.zh: DNA有这样的特性，不管你触碰了什么，无论你捡起了易拉罐，还是橡胶水管，都会留下一些自己的小痕迹。

yingyinNormal.en: Because, if something goes wrong, they could trace them straight back to us. Go wrong? This wasn't the fucking plan. I needed this to get our people back.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因为如果出事的话，他们就能直接找到我们头上。出事？计划他妈的不是这样的。我是要通过这个计划把我们的人救回来。

yingyinNormal.en: I called a friend of mine at the NYPD. The only Charles Wynn that died in the tri-state area this year did so in a car accident, no trace of aconitine in his blood.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我打电话给纽约警局的一位朋友，三州区域今年去世的"查尔斯·韦恩"只有一位，他是死于车祸，血液中未发现乌头碱。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, some people trace the Christmas tree back to the Egyptians, who used to bring green palm branches into their huts on the shortest day of the year, symbolizing life's triumph over death.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有些人说圣诞树源自古埃及，在每年白昼最短的日子，他们会把棕榈枝带进屋里象征生命战胜死亡。

yingyinNormal.en: By systematically comparing these features and looking for regular patterns of sound changes and correspondences between languages, linguists can determine relationships, trace specific steps in their evolution and even reconstruct earlier languages with no written records.
yingyinNormal.zh: 通过系统地比较这些特征，查找读音变化的常见形式和不同语言的对应关系，语言学家能们够确定它们之间的关系，追溯它们发展演变的详细过程，甚至重建没有文字记录的早期语言。

examination_example.sentence: In this brief period we may <highlight>trace</highlight> the beginning, growth, blossoming, and decay of many kinds of plays, and of many great careers
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在这个短暂的时期里，我们可以追溯许多种类的戏剧和许多伟大事业的兴起、发展、繁荣和衰落。

examination_example.sentence: In Oliver Twist, he <highlight>traces</highlight> an orphan's progress from the workhouse to the criminal slums of London.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在《雾都孤儿》中，他追溯了一个孤儿从济贫院到伦敦犯罪贫民窟的过程。

examination_example.sentence: If all humans share common origins, it seems reasonable to suppose that cultural diversity could also be <highlight>traced</highlight> to more constrained beginnings.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果所有人类都有共同的起源，那么似乎可以合理地推测，文化多样性也可以追溯到更有限的开端。
